org.jcvi.jillion.align

  • Packages that use org.jcvi.jillion.align 
    Package Description
    org.jcvi.jillion.align
    This package contains classes used to create or parse alignments.
    org.jcvi.jillion.align.pairwise
    This package contains classes for performing pair-wise alignments of two sequences.
    org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.align.blast  
    org.jcvi.jillion.internal.align  
    org.jcvi.jillion.trim.lucy
    This package contains trimmer implementations that follow the algorithms used by the TIGR program LUCY that was used to trim sanger reads.

    Class and Description
    AminoAcidSubstitutionMatrix
    AminoAcidSubstitutionMatrix is a marker interface for a SubstitutionMatrix of AminoAcids.
    NucleotideSubstitutionMatrix
    NucleotideSubstitutionMatrix is a marker interface for a SubstitutionMatrix of Nucleotides.
    NucleotideSubstitutionMatrixBuilder
    NucleotideSubstitutionMatrixBuilder is a Builder that will create new NucleotideSubstitutionMatrix instances using the given configuration.
    SequenceAlignment
    SequenceAlignment is an interface that describes an alignment between two Sequences.
    SubstitutionMatrix
    SubstitutionMatrix is a matrix that describes the rate at which one Residue changes into another over time.
